text: Big Horn County is a county in Northern Wyoming. The county seat is Basin. The largest city is Lovell. ==Communities== ===Towns=== *Basin (county seat) *Burlington *Byron *Cowley *Deaver *Frannie *Greybull *Lovell *Manderson ===Census-designated places=== *Hyattville *Shell ===Unincorporated communities=== *Emblem *Otto *Meadow Lark Lake ==Other websites== *Basin Republican Rustler - Local newspaper *Map of Otto Category:1897 establishments in the United States Category:19th-century establishments in Wyoming
